df_chikungunya = pd.read_csv('dadosrecifegov_casos-chikungunya2016.csv', sep=';')
df_dengue = pd.read_csv('dadosrecifegov_casos-dengue2016.csv', encoding='latin-1', sep=';')
df_zika = pd.read_csv('dadosrecifegov_casos-zika_2016.csv', sep=';')
df_bairros = pd.read_excel('BAIRROS-PE.xlsx')
df_estacoes = pd.read_excel('Todas as estações 2015 a 2017.xlsx')

As bases de dados apresentam diverentes quantidades de features.

  • Chikungunya = 91 features
  • Dengue = 121 features
  • Zika = 62 features
  • Bairros = 3 features com complemento dos bairros e estações
  • Estacoes = 7 features com dados complementares

2. Missing Values¶

Tratamento dos casos de missing.

In [33]:
def display_missing(df):
    print('{}'.format(df.name))
    for col in df.columns.tolist():          
        print('{} column missing values: {}'.format(col, df[col].isnull().sum()))
    print('\n')

In [107]:
plt.rcParams.update({'font.size': 10})
feature_importance = clf.feature_importances_
# make importances relative to max importance
feature_importance = 100.0 * (feature_importance / feature_importance.max())
sorted_idx = np.argsort(feature_importance)
pos = np.arange(sorted_idx.shape[0]) + .5
plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
plt.barh(pos, feature_importance[sorted_idx], align='center')
plt.yticks(pos,map(lambda x: names[x], sorted_idx))
plt.xlabel('Relative Importance')
plt.title('Variable Importance')
plt.show()
